<div class="docback">
<div class="note-source" id="TSJN-01-04-0071-sn"><p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ note, notes (memoranda, fragments, &amp;c.) ]">N</abbr> (<span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Library of Congress ]">DLC</span>); 2 p.; entirely in TJs hand.</p>
<p>This is a memorandum of executive agenda, together with militia estimates, probably drawn up immediately after TJ received news (see <a href="default.xqy?keys=TSJN-print-01-04-02-0062" class="document">Nelson to TJ, 21 Oct.</a>) that enemy troops had landed from the British fleet in Hampton Roads and were occupying adjacent points. A number of letters of the present and following dates show that TJ promptly carried out the plans here formulated.</p></div>
</div>
